CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1950, pg. 16, reads: "Downtown Get-Together - The Central YWCA, 59 Chatham Street, sponsored an interracial "get-together" on Tuesday night, Feb. 21, that was sparked by the presentation of an enjoyable program in auditorium. Dancing, movies and refreshments were also enjoyed.  Among those present were, left to right: Eleanore Zolatow, Aileen Faulkner, Vera Krulac, Mrs. Mattie Roberson, Clara Corbett, Olivia King, Mrs. Evelyn Cedel, Edna Mae Moon, Mrs. Eleanor Blystone and Helen Zebrasky.  Most of the women pictured represented various downtown department stores. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Eleanore Zolatow, Aileen Faulkner, Vera Krulac, Mattie Roberson, Clara Corbett, Olivia King, Evelyn Cedel, Edna Mae Moon, Eleanor Blystone, and Helen Zebrasky, standing behind table with refreshments in Central YWCA, Chatham Street
